text.tspan: Great reasons to support the openSUSE conference

flowRoot.flowPara: The annual openSUSE conference, located in Prague in 2012, attracted approximately 600 participants from a variety of open source projects. In collaboration with the local Linux community, SUSE and Gentoo we provided six concurrent tracks with talks, workshops and BoF sessions covering all levels of expertise. The live streamed session and all recorded session available on the openSUSE YouTube channel have been watched by thousands and the conference was the topic of numerous blogs and press articles.

The openSUSE community is a global community dedicated to developing and promoting openSUSE Linux. We work together in a friendly and open way, as part of the worldwide Free and Open Source Software community. We value trust, innovation and fun, and bring these core values to our events.

This year, the openSUSE conference (oSC 13) takes place at the Olympic Museum in Thessaloniki, Greece, from July 18 to July 22, 2013. A modern and welcoming venue in the city center, the Olympic Museum offers a great atmosphere for the expected 300+ attendees to enjoy the conference program and the networking opportunities.
